Artist: Arnold Newman (American, 1918 - 2006)

Medium: Gelatin silver print

Dimensions:

Image: 9 5/8 × 6 7/16 inches (24.46 × 16.31 cm)

Sheet: 9 15/16 × 7 15/16 inches (25.22 × 20.14 cm)

Credit Line: Gift of Howard and Ellen Greenberg

Object number: 2014.58.38

Signed: On sheet verso, center, artist's stamp in black ink: "© ARNOLD NEWMAN / THIS PHOTOGRAPH CANNOT BE COPIED OR REPRODUCED IN ANY FORM / WITHOUT THE EXPRESSED AND WRITTEN / PERMISSION OF THE PHOTOGRAPHER, IT / CAN BE USED FOR EXHIBIT PURPOSES ONLY. / 39 WEST 67TH ST., N.Y.C. 10023"

Inscribed: On sheet verso, center, in pencil: "Nabokov / 5257"

Markings: On sheet verso, bottom, in pencil: "PF113374-111"

Copyright: © Estate of Arnold Newman

DescriptionPortrait of Vladimir Nabokov and his wife Vera seated at a table having coffee in large room with crystal chandeliers. He's wearing a suit and tie while looking back over his shoulder.
